[[File:Entrance to Bedrock City, South Dakota.jpg|thumb|Entrance to Bedrock City]]
'''Flintstones Bedrock City''' is a 62-acre theme park and campground in [[Custer, South Dakota|Custer]], South Dakota in the [[Black Hills]] which features buildings and characters inspired by ''[[The Flintstones]]'' television series. The facility opened in 1966. It closed in 2015.<ref name=KOTA>{{cite web|url=http://www.kotatv.com/news/south-dakota-news/the-flintstones-bedrock-city-announces-its-closing/35083952 |title='The Flintstones Bedrock City' announces it's closing |author=Nicole Tschetter |date=September 3, 2015 |publisher=Schurz Communications |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151002144900/http://www.kotatv.com/news/south-dakota-news/the-flintstones-bedrock-city-announces-its-closing/35083952 |archivedate=2015-10-02 |df= }}</ref>

The [[Bedrock City (Arizona)|sister location in Arizona]] was put up for sale in 2015.<ref name=AO>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/inside-the-derelict-flintstones-theme-park-being-sold-for-2m|title=Inside the Derelict Flintstones Theme Park Being Sold for $2 Million|author=Rachel B. Doyle|date=June 10, 2015|publisher=Atlas Obscura}}</ref>

==Description==
{{unreferenced section|date=September 2015}}
[[File:Mount Rockmore, Bedrock City, South Dakota.jpg|thumb|Mount Rockmore]]
===Amusement Area===
The park's entrance includes a large gift shop, a drive-in restaurant which features Brontoburgers, and a 20-foot tall statue of [[Dino (The Flintstones)|Dino]] overlooking the entrance. After entering the park, visitors can ride a 1880s miniature train that takes guests to a western façade, through Dinosaur Canyon, around the park and returns to the depot after passing through a volcano called Mt. St. Wilma. Bedrock's City Hall welcomes visitors to the prehistoric town which includes the homes of the Flintstones, the Rubbles, Mr. Slate, and Mr. Granitebilt. Other features are a working movie cinema, playhouse theatre (featuring a show by the Flintstone Trio: Fred, Wilma, and Dino), radio station, telephone company, grocery store, police department, dentist's office, beauty parlor, stone scraper, fire department, Water Buffalo lodge, auto garage, and bank buildings. Interiors are decorated in the style of the show and feature sculpted and animated characters going about their daily lives in Bedrock. A feature at one end of Main Street is Mt. Rockmore, a replica of nearby [[Mt. Rushmore]] with the heads of Fred, Barney, Dino, and Mr. Granitebilt carved into a hill. The park also has a large playground with multiple unique activities
===Campground===
The campground is tucked away behind the park and includes a swimming pool, laundry/arcade, grocery store, putt-putt golf, playground, bathhouses, camping cabins and many campsites.

