{{Infobox toy | name = Bilofix | image = BILOfix crane.jpg | caption = Toy crane made with Bilofix | type = [[Construction set]] | country = Denmark | company = [[The Lego Group]] and Bilofix company | from = 1959 | to = 1960s }}
'''Bilofix''' is the name of a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[construction toy]] product primarily consisting of [[wood|wooden]] [[beams]] and [[plastic]] [[screw]]s and [[Bolt (fastener)|bolts]]. It was produced and marketed primarily in the 1960s first by the [[Lego company]] and then by a separate Bilofix company. The name Bilofix is usually written stylized as "BILOfix".
==History== The "Bilo" part of the name is a combination of the first three letters of [[Billund, Denmark|Billund]], [[Denmark]], birthplace of Lego and Bilofix, and the first initial of [[Ole Kirk Christiansen]], founder and inventor of Lego and Bilofix.<ref>[https://stadsarkiv.kolding.dk/administrator/components/com_koldingbogen/media/29b7a66f5102b6f53dcf88d713ebcbd0-2006-Legetoejsfabrikken-Bilofix.pdf Article about the history of Bilofix from the Kolding city archive] (danish)</ref> When LEGO decided in 1960 to stop producing wooden toys, two sons of Lego founder Ole Kirk Christiansen, Karl Georg and Gerhardt (brothers of [[Godtfred Kirk Christiansen]]), decided to leave the Lego company and to start Bilofix as their own independent business in a new factory in [[Kolding]], Denmark.<ref>[https://stadsarkiv.kolding.dk/administrator/components/com_koldingbogen/media/29b7a66f5102b6f53dcf88d713ebcbd0-2006-Legetoejsfabrikken-Bilofix.pdf Article about the history of Bilofix from the Kolding city archive] (danish)</ref>
